Why MIT License?
================

The MIT License was chosen for this project for the following reasons:

1. MAXIMUM ACADEMIC FREEDOM
   Researchers and students can freely use, modify, and build upon this
   work without restriction. Ideal for a research portfolio project
   intended to demonstrate capabilities to the academic community.

2. COMMERCIAL COMPATIBILITY
   FinTech companies and startups can integrate this platform into
   commercial products without licensing conflicts, encouraging
   real-world adoption and impact.

3. DEPENDENCY COMPATIBILITY
   All major dependencies (scikit-learn, XGBoost, LightGBM, SHAP, LIME,
   Fairlearn, AIF360, Evidently, MLflow, Streamlit, FastAPI) are
   compatible with MIT or more permissive licenses.

4. GITHUB COMMUNITY STANDARD
   MIT is the most popular open-source license on GitHub, maximizing
   discoverability, contributions, and community trust.

5. REGULATORY ALIGNMENT
   MIT's attribution requirement supports audit trail requirements
   under GDPR, EU AI Act, and financial regulatory frameworks
   (FCRA, ECOA) by ensuring proper attribution in derivative works.

6. PORTFOLIO VISIBILITY
   For resume and recruiter demonstration purposes, MIT ensures that
   any company reviewing this project can freely use it as a starting
   point without legal concern, increasing the likelihood of engagement.
